Project Notes
-------------

Instructions for Running:
cat <list> ./randomselection.pl -s15 -x2

Product Description:
This script takes lines of text on STDIN and outputs a random 
selection of records to STDOUT. -s is the sample size in percent.
-x tells the script to pick 'n' lines together as a 
single sample.
Perl script written by Andrew Nisbet for Edmonton Public Library, distributable by the enclosed license.

Repository Information:
This product is under version control using Git.

Dependencies:
None

Known Issues:
None
